parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes drag or grab
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
smoke comes from the wheels
the brakes are extremely hot to the touch
the brake warning light indicator is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to address recall notices can lead to unresolved safety issues, potentially causing accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Consumers receive recall notices but are unable to schedule appointments with dealerships
dealerships fail to contact consumers to schedule appointments
dealerships are unresponsive or uncooperative in addressing recall issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An overloaded electrical system can cause electrical fires, damage to electrical components, or even complete system failure, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Electrical system overload
tripped breakers or blown fuses
failure of electrical components such as televisions or power inverters
inability to operate electrical systems safely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic brake system can cause a loss of braking power, increasing the risk of accidents and potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loss of brake power
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal travels further than usual
vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
unusual noises or vibrations when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating and failure of the ignition switch can cause electrical fires, smoke, and burning odors, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. The malfunction can also leave the driver stranded, especially in motorhomes where the ignition system is critical for operation.
symptoms: The ignition key will not turn
the ignition switch overheats
distorts
and continues burning in place
pungent odor of burning electrical components
smoke coming from below the steering column
burnt wiring and connectors below the steering column.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overload of the electrical system can cause electrical fires, smoke, and burning odors, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. The malfunction can also leave the driver stranded, especially in motorhomes where the electrical system is critical for operation.
symptoms: Pungent odor of burning electrical components
smoke coming from below the steering column
burnt wiring and connectors below the steering column
ignition switch overheats
distorts
and continues burning in place.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Speed Control Deactivation Switch (SCDS) Recall and Repair Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to properly repair the SCDS can lead to unintended acceleration, which can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Unintended acceleration
sudden acceleration
loss of vehicle control
inability to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in repairing the SCDS can leave the vehicle in an unsafe condition, putting the driver and passengers at risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Unavailability of repair services
long wait times for repairs
lack of communication from dealerships or repair centers.
